{
  "texts": [
    "In case there is no such link we obtain the result by considering an intermediate equivalence with π X e ′′ for a suitable edge e ′′ such that there are links L 1 and L 2 with e = ∂ i L 1, e ′′ = ∂ f L 1 = ∂ i L 2 and e ′ = ∂ f L 2.",
    "Such an intermediate e ′′ can always be found.",
    "□ 7.4 Superselection criterion Proposition 7.10.",
    "The representations π X e for all e ∈ E and X ∈ Irr Z(C) satisfy the superselection criterion.Proof: We must show that for any cone Λ there is a unitary equivalenceπ X e | Λ ≃ u.e π 1 | Λ.Let C be a chain supported in the complement of Λ, so ρ X C (x) = x for all x ∈ A Λ.",
    "Then we have πX C | Λ = (π 1 • ρ X C)| Λ = π 1 | Λ."
  ]
}